---
import Doc from '../layouts/Doc.astro';
import FeatureRow from '../components/FeatureRow.astro';
import KPICard from '../components/KPICard.astro';
import Callout from '../components/Callout.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
import MonoLabel from '../components/MonoLabel.astro';
---

<Doc
  title="Chips for enterprises — ship your A2A agent in 4–8 hours"
  description="Mid-market DTC and retail enterprises with no internal agent capability. Self-serve via the Chips Studio. Agent ships in 4–8 hours, sharp from day 1 on Level B priors."
  pageLabel="FOR ENTERPRISES"
  eyebrow="CATEGORY A · MID-MARKET DTC + RETAIL"
  heading={`<em>Ship</em> your agent<br/>in <em>4–8 hours<span class="dot">.</span></em>`}
  lede="If you sell things online and you haven't shipped an agent yet, the gap between you and your better-funded competitors widens every week. Chips is to A2A agents what Shopify is to e-commerce sites."
>
  <section class="kpis">
    <div class="kpi-grid">
      <KPICard label="TIME TO LIVE AGENT" value="4–8" suffix="HOURS" detail="From signed contract to Agent Card published" />
      <KPICard label="BLENDED HANDSHAKE" value="$0.012" suffix="PER" detail="100K monthly handshakes · basic + standard tiers" />
      <KPICard label="CONVERSION LIFT" value="+16" suffix="PP" detail="Phase 1 cohort · outdoor &amp; athletic · vs. pre-network baseline" />
      <KPICard label="DAY-1 SHARPNESS" value="MONTH 6" suffix="EQUIVALENT" detail="Level B priors baked into your agent's system prompt from the first turn" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <FeatureRow number="01" label="THE PITCH" heading="Chips is to A2A agents what Shopify is to e-commerce sites.">
    <p>
      <em>Your agent ships in 4–8 hours</em>, recognizes every A2A-compliant consumer agent's user, bridges
      context across the network, and inherits behavior priors from the network so your agent is sharp on day 1.
    </p>
    <p>
      No infrastructure to build. No identity layer to design. No data warehouse to wire up. You bring your
      catalog and your policy; Chips brings the runtime, the bridge, the priors, and the rebate flow.
    </p>
  </FeatureRow>

  <FeatureRow number="02" label="THE STUDIO" heading="Catalog ingest. Policy YAML. Live A2A test harness. Learning tab.">
    <p>
      The Chips Studio is the enterprise console. <em>Catalog ingest</em> from OpenAPI, Shopify Storefront,
      NLWeb endpoint, or CSV. <em>Policy YAML editor</em> with live A2A test harness against your draft agent.
      <em>Bridge participation</em> toggles. <em>Operator dashboard.</em>
    </p>
    <p>
      The Learning tab is the differentiator. Level A view: your own Loop 1–3 state — consumer behavior
      summaries, SKU-level enrichment, policy refinements observed against your data. Level B view: the network
      priors your agent is currently consuming, with per-prior provenance (which aggregate distribution,
      N=, epsilon spent, version). Policy tuner: opt out of specific priors, weight your own Level A signal more
      heavily, or contribute additional signal categories.
    </p>
  </FeatureRow>

  <FeatureRow number="03" label="THE NETWORK" heading="Bridge in, priors out. Cold start solved.">
    <p>
      The consumer's relationship is with their consumer agent — ChatGPT, Claude, Apple Intelligence,
      Perplexity. Your agent never has to acquire them. <em>Standard A2A handshake delivers identity. Bridge
      delivers cross-enterprise context with consent. Network learning delivers behavior priors.</em>
    </p>
    <p>
      You arrive on the network and immediately benefit from every conversation that happened before yours.
      Late joiners benefit more, not less, from Level B priors — the priors are richer by then.
    </p>
  </FeatureRow>

  <FeatureRow number="04" label="THE PRICING" heading="Five meters. One bill. Bridge target side flips to revenue.">
    <p>
      <em>Handshake</em> per consumer ($0.001–$0.050 stratified by tier). <em>Bridge call</em> per query
      ($0.05–$1.00 stratified by scope). <em>Runtime subscription</em> per tenant ($99 / $999 / $5K+).
      <em>Network Intelligence</em> bundled into the runtime tier. Bridge target-side revenue share when other
      enterprises query your data: <strong>30% to you</strong>, 50% to the caller, 20% to Chips.
    </p>
    <p>
      Worked example, mid-market outdoor retailer: 100K monthly handshakes + 30K bridge calls + Growth runtime
      tier = <em>~$9,700/mo</em>. See <a href="/pricing">/pricing</a> for the full table.
    </p>
  </FeatureRow>

  <Callout variant="quote">
    <p>
      <strong>First cohort is outdoor &amp; athletic apparel.</strong> Bridge + Network Intelligence value
      compounds within each category, and we're picking verticals where the cross-enterprise read is
      structurally most valuable.
    </p>
    <p>
      Second cohort: beauty + skincare. Third: home goods. <em>Apply early for bootstrap pricing on bridge fees
      + introductory Network Intelligence</em> in exchange for being a launch reference.
    </p>
  </Callout>

  <section class="cta-row">
    <div class="cta-row-inner">
      <div>
        <MonoLabel tone="emerald">APPLY · COHORT IS CLOSING</MonoLabel>
        <h3 class="cta-h">
          Ten enterprises in the launch cohort.<br />
          <em>Six seats remain.</em>
        </h3>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <Button href="mailto:hello@chips.dev?subject=Chips%20cohort%20-%20enterprise" variant="primary">
          Apply to the cohort
        </Button>
        <Button href="/pricing" variant="outline">See pricing</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Doc>

<style>
  .kpis { margin-bottom: 64px; }
  .kpi-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    border: 1px solid var(--hair);
  }
  .cta-row {
    margin-top: 72px;
    padding: 48px 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hair);
  }
  .cta-row-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .cta-h {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 2vw + 0.5rem, 2.1rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 12px 0 0;
    max-width: 24ch;
  }
  .cta-h em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--emerald);
  }
  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: flex-end;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .kpi-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .cta-row-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cta-buttons { justify-content: flex-start; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .kpi-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
